<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="993" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d993">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Tower</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-02-12"><hi rend="italic">February 12,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 124.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 152, of November 18; No. 157, of November 25, and your No. 165, of
                            December 9 last, relative to the modification of the protocol for the
                            arbitration of the United States claims growing out of the Russian
                            seizures of American sealing and whaling vessels.</p>
                        <p>The Department awaits the result of its telegraphic instruction of
                            December 5 last relative thereto.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>